   "source": [
    "# Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC) Network Traffic Analysis & Anomaly Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "### Overview\n",
    "This notebook analyzes the **CIC-PQC-OAV-2025 dataset** to study how post-quantum cryptography (PQC) deployment affects encrypted network traffic and whether existing network intrusion detection systems (NIDS) misclassify it.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🎯 Key Objectives:\n",
    "1. **Traffic Analysis**: Statistical comparison between PQC and Classical traffic\n",
    "2. **Feature Engineering**: Domain-specific features (flow asymmetry, entropy delta, etc.)\n",
    "3. **Multi-stage Detection**: L1 rules → L2 thresholds → L3 ML ensemble\n",
    "4. **Class Imbalance**: SMOTE and DP-CTGAN resampling\n",
    "5. **Feature Selection**: ANOVA → Genetic Algorithm → Mutual Information + SHAP\n",
    "6. **Explainability**: SHAP and LIME analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📊 Dataset:\n",
    "- **Source**: https://www.unb.ca/cic/datasets/pqc-oav-dataset-2025.html\n",
    "- **Files**: \n",
    "  - `raw_sessions.jsonl`: 40,010 TLS sessions\n",
    "  - `ml_features_and_labels.csv`: ML-ready matrix with 32 features\n",
    "  - Scenario manifest for gray scenarios\n",
    "\n",
